          "body": "Verses 12-14 are not a generic devotional promise; they are a direct citation of the Deuteronomic covenant. Deuteronomy 4:29 — anticipating exile centuries before it happened — promised that when the exiled people \"seek the LORD your God, you will find Him, if you search for Him with all your heart and all your soul.\" Jeremiah 29:13 invokes that exact provision. The covenant has not been suspended by the exile; the covenant *anticipated* the exile and built in the mechanism of return. The exiles do not need the temple, the priesthood, or Jerusalem to find YHWH — they need to *seek Him with all the heart*. This is the seed of the synagogue, of personal piety apart from cult, and ultimately of the New Covenant's promise that God dwells with His people wherever they are (John 4:21-24)."
